EMAIL ANALYSIS – PHISHING EMAIL

Email Type: Phishing
Risk Level: High

Subject:
⚠️ Urgent: Your Account Will Be Locked

Phishing Indicators Identified:

1. Urgency & Fear Tactics
The email pressures the user to act immediately by threatening account suspension.

2. Suspicious URL
The link uses a fake verification domain:
http://secure-account-verify[.]com

3. Generic Greeting
The email uses “Dear User” instead of the recipient’s actual name.

4. Request for Sensitive Action
The user is asked to verify account details, which is a common phishing tactic.

5. Social Engineering Attempt
The message creates panic to manipulate the user into clicking the malicious link.

Conclusion:
This email should be classified as a phishing email because it contains multiple indicators commonly used in credential theft attacks.
